                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A good monk or Sk can pull vindi without his guards.  Our guild has done it serveral times now.  Appearently the guards still agro but if you pull him at the right time (don't ask me how) vindi will come and the guards won't.  
<br />

<br />
My question was mainly about pacify.  I know it works on the guards (that is it lands on them).  However, what I don't know for sure is the relationship between vindi and his guards. 
<br />

<br />
Is it:
<br />

<br />
a) Vindi and his guards are directly linked much in the same way a chanter and his pet is?  Thus, even pacifying his guards will cause them to agro if vindi is agroed?
<br />

<br />
b) The guards have an extremely large social range to vindi and even if they are a ways away they will aid him if he is attacked?  In this case perhaps paci would do the trick?
<br />

<br />
Normally this isn't an issue at all since our monk can pull him in short work.  However, last night we had a SK that was new to pulling him and it took us over an hour to finally get the single pull.  I offered to help try and paci the guards but they pretty much ignored me.  Finally after it was getting late, the guest chanter goes up and tries paci on the guards.  I find out from her that it worked (that is it landed) but the pullers insist vindi and his guards are directly linked so it didn't help.  I'm not one to assume someone is correct until I get 2nd and 3rd opinions.  Has anyone actually tried the paci approach?  Can you verify that paci is ineffective because they are directly linked like chanter pets?
<br />

<br />
Tyym</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
